Sentencas: A new bismuth-based perovskite cathode material, Bi0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Co0.2O3-delta (BiSFC), showing not only low area-specific resistance but also a low thermal expansion coefficient, exhibits excellent electrochemical catalytic activity for the oxygen reduction reaction in the application of intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells (ITSOFCs).
Titulo: Bismuth-Based Pervoskite as a High-Performance Cathode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The high performance implies that BiSFC is a very promising cathode material for ITSOFCs.
Titulo: Bismuth-Based Pervoskite as a High-Performance Cathode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells
